      "comment_id" : 67706236,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Of course it matches a single char, that&#39;s what that regexp does! What isn&#39;t clear however (and should not be the case either!) is that java puts the prefix <code>^</code> and suffix <code>$</code> around the provided regexp, altering it unwantedly and creating weird bugs. They should not do that, because that&#39;s not how the initial regexp was meant."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4804,
      "reputation" : 276251,
      "user_id" : 7412,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 96,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/doLQL.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "dogbane",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7412/dogbane"
